  <original-body>Method defined in the helper file which is alphabetically last of all helper files precedes over all other methods, even if used in other controllers' views.

Suppose Module ABC and XYZ are two modules having common helper method my_method. If we try to use my_method in ABC controller's views it uses my_method defined in XYZ helper. It should take my_method defined in ABC helper. 

I don't know if this is a bug or a limitation. Please clear.</original-body>
